parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
A client-generated, case-sensitive token that you can use to ensure the idempotency of the request. The token must be unique for each request.

It must be an ASCII string with a maximum length of 64 characters. For more information, see [How to ensure idempotence](~~25693~~).

>  If you do not specify this parameter, the system automatically uses the request ID as the client token. The request ID may be different for each request.

parameters.name: ExportId
parameters.description: The ID of the export directory for the protocol service.

parameters.name: FileSystemId
parameters.description:
The ID of the file system.

*   The IDs of CPFS file systems must start with `cpfs-`. Example: cpfs-125487\*\*\*\*.
*   The IDs of CPFS for Lingjun file systems must start with `bmcpfs-`. Example: bmcpfs-0015\*\*\*\*.
*   The IDs of CPFS SE file systems must start with `cpfsse-`. Example: cpfsse-022c71b134\*\*\*\*.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description:
The number of results for each query.

Valid values: 10 to 100. Default value: 20.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: A pagination token. It can be used in the next request to retrieve a new page of results.

parameters.name: ProtocolServiceId
parameters.description: The ID of the protocol service.
